      "writtenOn": "2026-06-18T14:44:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for reviewing @nobuto.murata@canonical.com. You are right that we could use the keystone\u0027s endpoint to get the public origin for the multi-region case. However, I shouldve been clearer in my commit message, CORS can also be an issue when subdomain mode is turned on in Traefik. If traefik is configured with routing_mode\u003dsubdomain, Keystone gets keystone.domain.tld and Horizon gets horizon.domain.tld, which are different origins",
